<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 10 — EIGENVALUES
═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="s10">
  <div class="section-num">Section 10</div>
  <h2>Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors — in matrix form</h2>

  <!-- DEFINITION -->
  <div class="def">
    <div class="def-title">Definition — Eigenvector and Eigenvalue</div>
    A vector <strong>|u⟩ ≠ 0</strong> is an <em>eigenvector</em> of matrix L with <em>eigenvalue</em> λ if:
    <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span>L |u⟩ = λ |u⟩</span></div></div>
    In explicit matrix form:
    <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span><strong>det(L − λI) = 0</strong></span><span class="eq-note">← characteristic equation</span></div><hr class="math-sep"><div style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.3rem;">For a 2×2 matrix:</div><div class="eq"><span>det</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-l">a−λ</td><td>b</td></tr><tr><td>c</td><td class="c-l">d−λ</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>= (a−λ)(d−λ) − b·c = 0</span></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Expanding:</div><div class="mstep-body">ad − aλ − dλ + λ² − bc = 0</div></div><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label"></div><div class="mstep-body"><strong>λ² − (a+d)λ + (ad−bc) = 0</strong> <span class="eq-note">← degree-2 polynomial</span></div></div></div>
    The matrix scales the vector by λ <strong>without changing its direction</strong>.
  </div>

  <canvas id="c_eigen" width="480" height="270"></canvas>
  <div class="canvas-caption">Generic vectors change direction; eigenvectors (coloured) stay on the same line — select the matrix</div>
  <div class="controls">
    <button class="btn sm" onclick="setEigenViz('Z')">Pauli Z</button>
    <button class="btn sm" onclick="setEigenViz('X')">Pauli X</button>
    <button class="btn sm" onclick="setEigenViz('H')">Hadamard H</button>
  </div>
  <div class="live" id="eigenLive" style="margin-top:0.4rem;"></div>

  <!-- STEP 1: characteristic equation -->
  <h3>Step 1 — Rewrite as a homogeneous system</h3>
  <p>Start from L|u⟩ = λ|u⟩ and move everything to the left. Recall that λ|u⟩ = λI|u⟩ where I is the identity matrix:</p>

  <div class="math-block"><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Start from:</div><div class="mstep-body">L|u⟩ = λ|u⟩</div></div><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Rearrange:</div><div class="mstep-body">L|u⟩ − λI|u⟩ = 0 &nbsp;→&nbsp; <strong>(L − λI)|u⟩ = 0</strong></div></div><hr class="math-sep"><div style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.4rem;">In matrix form:</div><div class="eq"><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-l">l₁₁−λ</td><td>l₁₂</td></tr><tr><td>l₂₁</td><td class="c-l">l₂₂−λ</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>·</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td>u₁</td></tr><tr><td>u₂</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span></div></div>

  <div class="note-box">
    Subtracting λI means subtracting λ only from the <strong>main diagonal</strong>, because I has 1 on the diagonal and 0 elsewhere:
    <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace; font-size:0.85rem; margin-top:0.4rem;">
    ( a  b )  −  λ( 1  0 )  =  ( a−λ   b  )<br>
    ( c  d )      ( 0  1 )     (  c    d−λ )
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 2: determinant -->
  <h3>Step 2 — Existence condition: det = 0</h3>
  <p>The system (L − λI)|u⟩ = 0 has a <strong>non-zero</strong> solution only if (L − λI) is <em>singular</em> (non-invertible). This occurs when the determinant is zero:</p>

  <div class="math-block">
  <div class="eq"><strong>det(L − λI) = 0</strong><span class="eq-note">&nbsp;&nbsp;← characteristic equation</span></div>
  <hr class="math-sep">
  <div style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.4rem;">For a 2×2 matrix:</div>
  <div class="eq">
    <span>det</span>
    <div class="mx"><div class="mx-body" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
      <div class="mx-cell lam">a−λ</div><div class="mx-cell">b</div>
      <div class="mx-cell">c</div><div class="mx-cell lam">d−λ</div>
    </div></div>
    <span>= (a−λ)(d−λ) − b·c = 0</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="math-sep">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Expanding:</div><div class="mstep-body">ad − aλ − dλ + λ² − bc = 0</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">&nbsp;</div><div class="mstep-body"><strong>λ² − (a+d)λ + (ad−bc) = 0</strong><span class="eq-note">&nbsp;← polynomial of degree 2</span></div></div>
</div>

  <div class="note-box">
    For a matrix N×N the characteristic equation is a polynomial of degree N in λ → there are always N eigenvalues (counting multiplicities), possibly complex.
  </div>

  <!-- Example: Pauli Z -->
  <h3>Full example — Pauli Z, all steps</h3>

  <p><strong>Step 1</strong> — Write the matrix:</p>
  <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span>Z =</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-n">−1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span></div></div>

  <p><strong>Step 2</strong> — Calculate Z − λI by subtracting λ from the diagonal:</p>
  <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span>Z − λI =</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-n">−1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>− λ ·</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td>1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-l">1−λ</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-l">−1−λ</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span></div></div>

  <p><strong>Step 3</strong> — Calculate the determinant (diagonal matrix: product of diagonal elements):</p>
  <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span>det(Z − λI) = (1−λ)·(−1−λ)</span></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Expanding:</div><div class="mstep-body">(1−λ)(−1−λ) = −1 − λ + λ + λ²</div></div><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label"></div><div class="mstep-body">= <strong>λ² − 1</strong></div></div></div>

  <p><strong>Step 4</strong> — Solve the characteristic equation:</p>
  <div class="math-block"><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label"></div><div class="mstep-body">λ² − 1 = 0 &nbsp;→&nbsp; λ² = 1 &nbsp;→&nbsp; λ = ±1</div></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="eq"><span><span class="eq-arrow">→</span></span><span>λ₁ = <strong>+1</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; λ₂ = <strong>−1</strong></span></div></div>

  <!-- FINDING EIGENVECTORS -->
  <h3>Step 3 — Finding the eigenvectors</h3>
  <p>For each eigenvalue λₖ, substitute into (L − λₖI) and solve (L − λₖI)|u⟩ = 0:</p>

  <p><strong>Case λ₁ = +1</strong> — substitute λ=+1:</p>
  <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-l">1−1</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-l">−1−1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-n">−2</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>·</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td>u₁</td></tr><tr><td>u₂</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">row 1:</div><div class="mstep-body">0·u₁ + 0·u₂ = 0 &nbsp;→&nbsp; u₁ free</div></div><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">row 2:</div><div class="mstep-body">−2·u₂ = 0 &nbsp;→&nbsp; <strong>u₂ = 0</strong></div></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="eq"><span>Choose u₁=1 &nbsp;→&nbsp; |u₁⟩ =</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td>1</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>= |0⟩ ✓</span></div></div>

  <p><strong>Case λ₂ = −1</strong> — substitute λ=−1:</p>
  <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-l">1+1</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-l">−1+1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td>2</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td><td class="c-0">0</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>·</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td>u₁</td></tr><tr><td>u₂</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">row 1:</div><div class="mstep-body">2·u₁ = 0 &nbsp;→&nbsp; <strong>u₁ = 0</strong></div></div><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">row 2:</div><div class="mstep-body">0 = 0 &nbsp;→&nbsp; u₂ free</div></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="eq"><span>Choose u₂=1 &nbsp;→&nbsp; |u₂⟩ =</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td>1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>= |1⟩ ✓</span></div></div>

  <!-- EXAMPLE: Pauli X -->
  <h3>Second example — Pauli X, non-trivial eigenvectors</h3>
  <p>Gate X has the same eigenvalues as Z (±1) but different and more interesting eigenvectors:</p>

  <p><strong>Steps 1–4</strong> — Eigenvalues (computed above): λ₁ = +1, λ₂ = −1</p>

  <p><strong>Eigenvector for λ₁ = +1</strong>:</p>
  <div class="math-block"><div class="eq"><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-l">0−1</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td class="c-l">0−1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="mx"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-n">−1</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td class="c-n">−1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>·</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td>u₁</td></tr><tr><td>u₂</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr><tr><td class="c-0">0</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">row 1:</div><div class="mstep-body">−u₁ + u₂ = 0 &nbsp;→&nbsp; <strong>u₂ = u₁</strong></div></div><hr class="math-sep"><div class="eq"><span>u₁=1, u₂=1. Normalize:</span></div><div class="eq"><span>|u₁⟩ =</span><span><span class="scalar">1/√2</span> ·</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>1</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>=</span><span><span class="vec"><table><tbody><tr><td>1/√2</td></tr><tr><td>1/√2</td></tr></tbody></table></span></span><span>= |+⟩</span></div></div>

  <p><strong>Eigenvector for λ₂ = −1</strong>:</p>
  <div class="math-block">
  <div class="eq">
